headline: Abbott (ABT) Margin Surge Reinforces Bullish Narratives Despite Earnings Decline Forecast
summary: Abbott Laboratories (ABT) reported net profit margins of 31.8%, a significant jump from last year’s 14%. EPS grew sharply over the past year, up 142%, well above its five-year average annual growth rate of 18.1%. Despite this exceptional profit performance, the earnings outlook now points to a forecast decline of 7.1% per year over the next three years, setting up a tension between recent growth and future expectations.
